label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for major salivary gland cancer.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The assessment of primary salivary gland tumors includes a pertinent history, (pain, trismus, etc.), inspection, palpation, and evaluation of the cranial nerves.  Radiologic studies may add information valuable for staging.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Stage III Testicular Mixed Germ Cell Tumor AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage III includes: Any pT/TX, Any N, M1, SX.  M1: Distant metastasis. SX: Marker studies not available or not performed.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with mucosal disease. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with moderately advanced disease.  Tumor involves deep soft tissue, cartilage, bone, or overlying skin. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with very advanced disease.  Tumor involves brain, dura, skull base, lower cranial nerves (IX, X, XI, XII), masticator space, carotid artery, prevertebral space, or mediastinal structures. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with no metastases to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with regional lymph node metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for mucosal melanoma of the head and neck.

label.value: Stage I Testicular Immature Teratoma AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage I includes: pT1-4, N0, M0, SX.  pT1: Tumor limited to the testis and epididymis without vascular/lymphatic invasion; tumor may invade into the tunica albuginea but not the tunica vaginalis.  pT2: Tumor limited to the testis and epididymis with vascular/lymphatic invasion, or tumor extending through the tunica albuginea with involvement of the tunica vaginalis.  pT3: Tumor invades the spermatic cord with or without vascular/lymphatic invasion.  pT4: Tumor invades the scrotum with or without vascular/lymphatic invasion.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  SX: Marker studies not available or not performed. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of mucosal melanoma of the head and neck, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mucosal Melanoma of the Head and Neck cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Mucosal melanoma of the head and neck with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Both the histologic diagnosis and the age of the patient are of such importance in the behavior and prognosis of thyroid cancer that these factors are included in this staging system. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The pathologic staging requires the use of all information obtained in the clinical staging, as well as histologic study of the surgically resected specimens.  The surgeon's description of gross unresected residual tumor must also be included.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.  Note: All categories may be subdivided: (s) solitary tumors and (m) multifocal tumor (the largest determines the classification) (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with a tumor size of 1 cm or less in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with a tumor size of more than 1 cm but not more than 2 cm in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage II Testicular Immature Teratoma AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage II includes: Any pT/TX, N1-3, M0, SX.  pTX: Primary tumor cannot be assessed.  N1: Metastasis with a lymph node mass 2 cm or less in greatest dimension; or multiple lymph nodes, none more than 2cm in greatest dimension.  N2: Metastasis with a lymph node mass more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension; or multiple lymph nodes, any one mass greater than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  N3: Metastasis with a lymph node mass more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. M0: No distant metastasis. SX: Marker studies not available or not performed.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with moderately advanced local disease.  Tumor of any size extending beyond the thyroid gland capsule to invade subcutaneous soft tissues, larynx, trachea, esophagus, or recurrent laryngeal nerve. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT4a Anaplastic Carcinoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrathyroidal anaplastic carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with very advanced disease.  Tumor invades prevertebral fascia or encases carotid artery or mediastinal vessels.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pT4b Anaplastic Carcinoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: Anaplastic carcinoma with gross extrathyroid extension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Thyroid Cancer pN1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with metastasis to unilateral, bilateral or contralateral cervical (Levels I, II, III, IV, or V) or retropharyngeal or superior mediastinal lymph nodes (Level VII). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for thyroid cancer.

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The assessment of a thyroid tumor depends on inspection and palpation of the thyroid gland and regional lymph nodes.  Indirect laryngoscopy to evaluate vocal cord motion is essential.  A variety of imaging procedures can provide additional useful information.  These include radioisotope thyroid scans, ultrasonography, computed tomography scans (CT), magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scans, and PET scans.  The diagnosis of thyroid cancer must be confirmed by needle biopsy or open biopsy of the tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of thyroid cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Thyroid Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Testicular Immature Teratoma AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage III includes: Any pT/TX, Any N, M1, SX.  M1: Distant metastasis. SX: Marker studies not available or not performed.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Thyroid Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Thyroid cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Congenital Amegakaryocytosis

value.value: A rare disorder of infancy characterized by marked reduction or absence of megakaryocytes and thrombocytopenia.

label.value: Genitourinary System Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of genitourinary system cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Penile Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of penile cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Primary urethral carcinomas and melanomas are not included in this classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Penile Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of penile cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete resection of the primary site with appropriate margins is required for pathologic classification.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Penile Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of penile cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Penile Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Penile cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Penile Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Penile cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Penile Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Penile cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Penile Cancer pTa TNM Finding v7

value.value: Penile cancer with a finding of noninvasive verrucous carcinoma.  Note: Broad pushing penetration (invasion) is permitted; destructive invasion is against this diagnosis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
